== 6. Ne5 · Central Variation ==
White places their knight into the center to recapture the pawn on c4 while leaving the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop open. There are two theoretical responses for Black.

'''[[/6...Nbd7/]]''' is the main move, letting White take on c4 and preparing to either put the knight on b6 or to play e5.

'''[[/6...e6/]]''' is the Wiesbaden variation. This line involves White attempting to gain a lot of initiative and Black preventing it by sacrificing a piece for three pawns, generally leading to an endgame where Black tries to march an army of pawns down the board.

